NAME
     ffind - find files for a certain pattern in a  given  direc-
     tory.

SYNOPSIS
     call ffind (_p_a_t_h, _f_i_l_e_s, _f_i_l_t_e_r, _n, _i_n_s_u_b)

DESCRIPTION
     ffind is an interface to call unix/linux command `find`.

     _p_a_t_h this is the input path [input].

     _f_i_l_e_s
          this is found files names [output].

     _f_i_l_t_e_r
          file filter for "-name" matching pattern [input].

     _n    number of files found [output].

     _i_n_s_u_b
          a logical variable to specify whether  search  in  sub-
          directories. This option is OS-dependant. [input].

OPTIONS
     NONE.

EXAMPLES
      character*512 fullname,path
      file='/usr/local/test/bjfs.xyz'
      call getpathname(fullname,path)

      file should be "/usr/local/test"

